   {:e #blake3 "1f505228f522d5152db1ce1c57e9c31e3fdf2a5571b0f359af22a1ac5152e795" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: The seed assembles context using alpha*relevance + beta*significance + gamma*recency scoring. It doesn't model convergence across independent sources, corroboration strength, or dependency structure. After a multi-agent audit, the seed should surface 'here are the 5 findings all agents agree on, ranked by severity x corroboration, with their dependency chain' — not a keyword-matched grab bag. RATIONALE: The seed is the agent's window into accumulated knowledge. If it can't surface second-order structure (convergence, contradiction, dependencies), the agent falls back to reading documents — defeating the harvest/seed lifecycle. This is the integration task that makes C9-1 and C9-2 visible to the agent. APPROACH: (1) In seed.rs assemble(), add a corroboration_boost term to scoring: score = alpha*relevance + beta*significance + gamma*recency + delta*corroboration. Default delta=0.4 (strong signal). (2) When building ContextSections, group observations by concept cluster. For each cluster with corroboration >= 2 agents, create a ContextSection::ConvergentFinding with: finding summary (cluster centroid text), corroboration score, confidence range, agent list, and dependency chain summary. (3) ConvergentFinding sections get OutputPrecedence::System (never truncated by budget). (4) Limit to top-5 convergent findings to prevent context bloat. (5) Include a 'contradictions' subsection for clusters where agents disagree (from C9-4). ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid seed --task 'determine path forward' surfaces F(S) monotonicity finding (4/4 corroboration) in the first section. (B) Convergent findings appear before single-agent observations. (C) Dependency chain is visible in seed output. (D) Budget truncation never removes convergent findings. CONSIDERATIONS: The corroboration boost must not cause stale findings to dominate indefinitely. Add a decay factor: corroboration_boost *= freshness(cluster_mean_timestamp). Old convergent findings still outrank new single-agent findings, but eventually decay. DEPENDS-ON: C9-1 (t-6090a2ed), C9-2 (t-03f867f7). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/seed.rs." :op :assert}
